The medical journal JAMA Internal Medicine recently published an interesting article entitled &ldquo;Shared Understanding With Patients.&rdquo;
As a Houston, Texas medical malpractice attorney, the title of this article captured my attention. Time after time, I meet with new clients who have been seriously injured from poor medical care who say something like, &ldquo;If the doctor (or nurse) would have just listened, this never would have happened.&rdquo;
Poor communication during treatment
